quoteEn:
Throw greed, envy and grudge away from your heart;
Abandon your bad habits and thoughts.
Denying gives you harm, so deny less;
Affirmation is helpful for you, so increase your affirmation.

Man's sole breath is worth a soul;
His exclusive hair is worth a mine.
However, there is another kind of man, let alone speak with him; Seeing not him is worthy of the world's wealth.

If your hands do not work, try to work with your feet;
If your feet reject to work, then shout, call out...
If you do not have a voice to shout, then try to work with your intellect;
In short, show sincerity and loyalty in every breath you take.

O, Joseph! You do find peace in your father's house;
Valley and brothers mean death and danger for you.
Neither make peace with the wolf nor sit with the envious people;
The envious wolf is worse than the wolf outside.
